# Data Table Conventions

## Search Pattern

Each data table gets a single search input, scoped to one explicitly-designated text column — never inferred from column position or implemented as a global multi-column search.

- Designate the searchable column explicitly in the table's column config (e.g. a `searchable: true` flag or equivalent), not by assuming "first column."
- Filter via substring match on that one column.
- Non-text filters (booleans, enums, dates) are separate controls (dropdown, toggle, date picker) — never folded into the search box.

**Why:** global multi-column search is ambiguous to the user (unclear what matched) and doesn't generalize to non-string columns or server-side queries without expensive `OR ILIKE` scans across every column.

## Pagination Pattern

Every data table paginates server-side. Never load an unbounded result set.

- Controls: Next/Previous only — no numbered page strip. Avoids requiring a total-row-count query, and generalizes to data sources (e.g. Supabase admin API) that don't cheaply expose totals.
- Page size: fixed at 50 rows. No user-facing page-size selector.
- Layout: table grows naturally; the page scrolls. No fixed-height internal scroll region on the table body.

